The Vice President of the United States, Mike Pence, attended the unveiling of Lordstown Motors' new fully electric pickup truck, the Lordstown Endurance, in Lordstown, Ohio. Pence commended the company for bringing jobs back to the area and highlighted President Trump's commitment to American manufacturing. He also praised the resilience and character of the Mahoning Valley community. Pence discussed the administration's response to the COVID-19 pandemic and the efforts to reopen the economy. He noted the recent increase in jobs and retail sales, signaling a strong recovery. Pence emphasized the importance of American manufacturing and praised the workers in the Mahoning Valley for their contribution to the industry. He expressed confidence in Lordstown Motors' future success and the positive impact it will have on the community.